1
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:27,040
[Age of Awakening]

2
00:01:27,040 --> 00:01:30,120
[Episode One]

3
00:01:40,695 --> 00:01:42,160
In 1915,

4
00:01:43,123 --> 00:01:44,520
World War I

5
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:46,760
entered its second year of unprecedented tragedy.

6
00:01:48,226 --> 00:01:51,080
While Germany was distracted in Europe,

7
00:01:51,316 --> 00:01:54,120
Japan stepped up its expansion in China.

8
00:01:55,203 --> 00:01:56,520
Before and after

9
00:01:56,863 --> 00:01:58,600
the failure of the Second Revolution,

10
00:01:58,694 --> 00:02:01,480
Sun Zhongshan and others were forced into exile overseas.

11
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,520
Bourgeois revolutionaries

12
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:08,000
were unable to carry out the anti-imperialist and anti-feudal struggle to the end.

13
00:02:08,826 --> 00:02:10,440
With political chaos at home,

14
00:02:10,543 --> 00:02:13,080
the suffering of the people,

15
00:02:13,241 --> 00:02:15,040
and internal and external troubles,

16
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:19,760
China was once again thrown into a tumultuous situation.

17
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,400
Mr President,

18
00:03:21,343 --> 00:03:23,880
Japanese Minister Hijiyoshi has sent an ultimatum

19
00:03:24,388 --> 00:03:26,040
to be replied within 48 hours.

20
00:03:26,618 --> 00:03:29,000
[Yuan Shikai, President of the Republic of China]
What does the ultimatum say?

21
00:03:29,414 --> 00:03:30,720
[Liang Shiyi, styled Yifu, Premier of the Republic of China]
If we do not reply within the time limit,

22
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,640
[Liang Shiyi, styled Yifu, Premier of the Republic of China]
nor accept the Twenty-One Demands,

23
00:03:32,162 --> 00:03:35,760
[Cao Rulin, styled Yuntian, Vice Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of China]
then Japan will take necessary measures.

24
00:03:36,689 --> 00:03:37,680
What does he want?

25
00:03:37,984 --> 00:03:38,880
Hijiyoshi said:

26
00:03:38,971 --> 00:03:41,640
Japan is to take over Shandong in the northeast.

27
00:03:46,652 --> 00:03:51,800
Japanese... They still want us dead.

28
00:03:52,271 --> 00:03:53,920
This afternoon, the Ministry of War have reported

29
00:03:54,396 --> 00:03:55,596
signs that the Japanese navy

30
00:03:56,171 --> 00:03:58,640
is heading to our southeast coast.

31
00:03:59,039 --> 00:03:59,840
What?

32
00:04:01,172 --> 00:04:03,000
Does he want a war?

33
00:04:03,749 --> 00:04:04,960
Make no mistake:

34
00:04:05,340 --> 00:04:06,840
I am Yuan Shikai,

35
00:04:07,498 --> 00:04:09,160
not Li Hongzhang.

36
00:04:09,548 --> 00:04:11,120
For a long time, there have been discussions in Japan

37
00:04:11,426 --> 00:04:12,360
advocating for Japanese intervention

38
00:04:12,587 --> 00:04:15,200
in our country's Yangtze River basin as soon as possible.

39
00:04:17,132 --> 00:04:20,080
Stupid... Stupid...

40
00:04:20,993 --> 00:04:22,280
You didn't tell Hijikata that

41
00:04:22,350 --> 00:04:25,350
it's not that I, Yuan Shikai, who disagreed with the Twenty-One demands.

42
00:04:25,638 --> 00:04:27,680
It's the people who are rebelling so much.

43
00:04:27,918 --> 00:04:30,800
It was them who hid Sun Zhongshan and Huang Xing in Japan.

44
00:04:31,131 --> 00:04:33,520
Didn't they also say they should respect public opinion?

45
00:04:34,011 --> 00:04:35,360
Our plea attempts have worked.

46
00:04:35,873 --> 00:04:37,840
The Japanese agreed to our demands in Article 5,

47
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,040
which we can discuss later.

48
00:04:39,383 --> 00:04:42,383
But... the treaty must be signed immediately.

49
00:04:55,069 --> 00:04:57,960
What is your Foreign Ministry's response?

50
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:01,960
The Ministry of Foreign Affairs obeys the orders of the President.

51
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:03,160
Nicely said.

52
00:05:03,978 --> 00:05:05,800
Then accept the Japanese terms.

53
00:05:07,111 --> 00:05:11,800
Now Sun Zhongshan, Huang Xing and the others will make trouble again.

54
00:05:12,411 --> 00:05:14,080
These people all kneel overseas.

55
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,160
It won't be a big deal.

56
00:05:16,099 --> 00:05:16,600
Right.

57
00:05:17,621 --> 00:05:20,680
Yuntian, tell the Japanese:

58
00:05:21,269 --> 00:05:22,480
the treaty will be signed,

59
00:05:23,311 --> 00:05:25,840
but Article 5 of the demands will not be accepted.

60
00:05:26,523 --> 00:05:27,880
This is the bottom line.

61
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,920
I gave him respect,

62
00:05:30,183 --> 00:05:31,960
he should also give me some.

63
00:05:32,243 --> 00:05:33,560
Understood, Mr President.

64
00:05:34,268 --> 00:05:36,360
What is the deadline for the Japanese?

65
00:05:36,943 --> 00:05:37,520
Nine days.

66
00:05:38,023 --> 00:05:39,640
Then wait until the night of the ninth day

67
00:05:40,104 --> 00:05:41,360
to screw the Japanese.

68
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,960
Extra! Extra!

69
00:05:44,303 --> 00:05:46,280
Today's extra is really strange!

70
00:05:46,464 --> 00:05:48,320
President Yuan Shikai

71
00:05:48,518 --> 00:05:50,560
is selling out the country!

72
00:05:50,906 --> 00:05:52,760
This disgrace! Sells, sells, sells!

73
00:05:53,196 --> 00:05:55,320
His back is not afraid to straighten up,

74
00:05:55,634 --> 00:05:57,600
but the people of the country do not agree!

75
00:05:57,823 --> 00:05:59,600
His anger is nowhere to be seen!

76
00:05:59,703 --> 00:06:02,703
Look at this woman! So angry, she steps on the extra!

77
00:06:03,023 --> 00:06:06,360
Look at this man! So angry, he breaks his crutch!

78
00:06:09,503 --> 00:06:11,920
9th May, 1915

79
00:06:12,349 --> 00:06:13,720
By order of Yuan Shikai,

80
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:15,120
an agreement is signed with Japan:

81
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:17,560
the Twenty-One Demands which humiliated the country.

82
00:06:17,662 --> 00:06:18,880
According to this treaty,

83
00:06:19,064 --> 00:06:21,000
China recognized Japan's inheritence of

84
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,480
all German rights and interests in Shandong.

85
00:06:23,574 --> 00:06:26,200
Japan in southern Manchuria and eastern Mongolia in China

86
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,680
enjoyed special rights.

87
00:06:28,423 --> 00:06:29,520
Japan gets in China

88
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:31,800
various railway construction rights, and so on.

89
00:06:32,565 --> 00:06:34,520
The Beiyang government's sell-out

90
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:37,280
was strongly opposed by the nation.

91
00:06:37,348 --> 00:06:38,440
All major cities in China,

92
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:40,960
like Beijing, Guangzhou, Wuhan,

93
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:42,120
Qingdao, and other places

94
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:44,880
all held huge demonstrations.

95
00:06:44,983 --> 00:06:47,320
Shanghai dockers went on strike

96
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,640
announcing a boycott of Japanese goods.

97
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:52,120
Workers in Hankow, Zhenjiang, Hanyang, Changsha,

98
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,480
Fuzhou and other places

99
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,880
held various protests one after another.

100
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,240
Refusing to recognise the Twenty-One Demands

101
00:06:58,353 --> 00:06:59,600
and vowing to avenge national humiliation

102
00:06:59,958 --> 00:07:02,400
demonstrates a strong anti-imperialist stance

103
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,560
and a strong patriotic passion.

104
00:07:04,754 --> 00:07:07,754
Sun Zhongshan, Huang Xing and others in exile overseas

105
00:07:07,754 --> 00:07:11,040
call for revolutionaries to return to China to oppose Yuan.

106
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:16,280
[Waseda University, Japan]

107
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:16,920
[Waseda University, Japan]
Quick! Read this!

108
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:17,096
[Waseda University, Japan]

109
00:07:17,096 --> 00:07:18,000
[Waseda University, Japan]
Latest news from home!

110
00:07:21,134 --> 00:07:23,800
[Li Dazhao, styled Shou Chang, Waseda University student]
Shameless! Insane!

111
00:07:24,237 --> 00:07:25,320
We have fought for so long

112
00:07:25,697 --> 00:07:26,760
[Gao Yihan, Waseda University student]
and this is what we get.

113
00:07:27,256 --> 00:07:29,360
Is there really no way out for us?

114
00:07:30,710 --> 00:07:31,760
Big deal.

115
00:07:32,014 --> 00:07:33,440
It's not for you or me to decide.

116
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:35,360
Let's take it easy, let's eat first.

117
00:07:35,688 --> 00:07:37,120
When the country's at stake, there is no time to eat.

118
00:07:37,387 --> 00:07:38,640
You say you vow to fight back for the country,

119
00:07:38,855 --> 00:07:40,840
how... how can you still eat?

120
00:07:41,055 --> 00:07:42,080
You can't even eat!

121
00:07:50,519 --> 00:07:52,920
Students! Countrymen!

122
00:07:54,031 --> 00:07:56,000
The sky's the limit, the war clouds fly.

123
00:07:57,271 --> 00:07:59,680
The Japanese seize their chance, and force our Xia Yu.

124
00:07:59,899 --> 00:08:02,320
Students in Japan, detained in a foreign land.

125
00:08:02,526 --> 00:08:06,400
Looking back at China, at the sky sorrowful and enraged!

126
00:08:06,792 --> 00:08:09,792
Now that our country has fallen and our people have died,

127
00:08:10,494 --> 00:08:13,160
there is no longer any fear to speak out.

128
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:16,440
We should have the determination to break through.

129
00:08:17,343 --> 00:08:19,080
Yuan Shikai, the thief of the country.

130
00:08:19,555 --> 00:08:21,560
He wants to become emperor by restoring the imperial system.

131
00:08:22,104 --> 00:08:25,040
The Republic of China is in danger!

132
00:08:25,398 --> 00:08:27,040
The traitor Yuan Shikai

133
00:08:27,587 --> 00:08:29,560
has signed the Twenty-One Demands.

134
00:08:30,108 --> 00:08:34,120
The Chinese nation is in danger!

135
00:08:34,706 --> 00:08:37,360
Fellow countrymen, the Republic is dying.

136
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:39,760
Qingdao is about to be lost.

137
00:08:40,467 --> 00:08:43,800
Fellow countrymen, what do we say?

138
00:08:44,437 --> 00:08:48,320
Let's go home! Let's go home!

139
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:50,000
Down with Yuan! Let's go home!

140
00:08:50,277 --> 00:08:50,840
Let's go home!

141
00:08:51,308 --> 00:08:51,920
Down with Yuan!

142
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,880
Alright, don't be sorry.

143
00:08:54,563 --> 00:08:57,320
It's up to you guys to overthrow Yuan.

144
00:08:57,702 --> 00:08:59,000
Don't make trouble for the country.

145
00:08:59,272 --> 00:09:00,800
What did you say?

146
00:09:02,029 --> 00:09:02,840
Zhang Fengzai,

147
00:09:02,909 --> 00:09:05,760
now that the country is in trouble and the republic is dying

148
00:09:06,025 --> 00:09:07,760
you're all being a bit sly here.

149
00:09:08,553 --> 00:09:09,840
Are you still Chinese?

150
00:09:10,105 --> 00:09:11,880
Do you have any patriotism left in you?

151
00:09:11,993 --> 00:09:13,760
That's right! Are you Chinese?!

152
00:09:13,868 --> 00:09:14,800
China is now in this state,

153
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:16,240
has been for much more than a day or two ago.

154
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,720
Can you save the country with this?

155
00:09:17,889 --> 00:09:20,520
It's all because of you knuckleheads!

156
00:09:20,743 --> 00:09:22,960
China is in such a sorry state!

157
00:09:23,239 --> 00:09:25,400
Yeah! The prisoners are you!

158
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,600
Prisoners? Us?

159
00:09:29,352 --> 00:09:32,320
We won't go along with this accusation.

160
00:09:33,549 --> 00:09:35,440
If it weren't for those stupid revolutionaries.

161
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:38,440
Had they not wanted to copy the American republican system,

162
00:09:38,623 --> 00:09:41,080
China would have been a constitutional monarchy.

163
00:09:41,606 --> 00:09:42,560
It wouldn't have turned out to be

164
00:09:42,643 --> 00:09:44,240
the grotesque situation we find ourselves in today.

165
00:09:44,824 --> 00:09:46,920
Yuan Shikai's attempt to introduce a constitutional monarchy

166
00:09:47,145 --> 00:09:49,080
was a real return to the right track.

167
00:09:49,573 --> 00:09:51,600
This is the way to save China.

168
00:09:51,638 --> 00:09:52,760
The foundation of prosperity.

169
00:09:52,931 --> 00:09:53,960
Nonsense!

170
00:09:54,024 --> 00:09:55,960
Ridiculous! Ridiculous!

171
00:09:56,024 --> 00:09:57,320
The idea of a democratic republic

172
00:09:57,637 --> 00:09:58,920
is already well established.

173
00:09:59,103 --> 00:10:00,600
Aren't you driving backwards in history?

174
00:10:00,756 --> 00:10:03,756
Yeah! That's right! Driving backwards!

175
00:10:04,095 --> 00:10:06,760
We are the ones driving backwards in history?

176
00:10:06,949 --> 00:10:08,600
Or is it you revolutionaries?

177
00:10:08,788 --> 00:10:10,880
Ignoring China's national conditions!

178
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:13,320
Students! Countrymen!

179
00:10:13,646 --> 00:10:15,520
Kang Youwei has long said:

180
00:10:15,709 --> 00:10:17,760
a revolution is not a good thing for a country.

181
00:10:18,542 --> 00:10:19,440
The French Revolution:

182
00:10:19,784 --> 00:10:22,000
eighty years of turmoil and bloodshed of millions.

183
00:10:22,589 --> 00:10:25,360
Furthermore, the Chinese people are not yet open-minded.

184
00:10:25,948 --> 00:10:26,880
In this case,

185
00:10:27,121 --> 00:10:28,760
the forced imposition of a republican system

186
00:10:28,828 --> 00:10:31,400
will be like a floating duck on water, with no roots.

187
00:10:31,744 --> 00:10:34,360
Zhang Fengzai, what you just said

188
00:10:34,549 --> 00:10:36,040
is absolutely absurd!

189
00:10:36,997 --> 00:10:38,000
The words of Kang Youwei

190
00:10:38,434 --> 00:10:40,600
have been refuted by many revolutionary martyrs.

191
00:10:41,222 --> 00:10:42,520
Of course the revolution will shed blood.

192
00:10:42,848 --> 00:10:44,400
But I would like to ask you:

193
00:10:44,719 --> 00:10:48,040
if a monarch is established first, will there be no bloodshed?

194
00:10:48,344 --> 00:10:48,800
Right!

195
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:49,442
[Zhang Tuzhao, styled Xing Yan, prominent social activist forced into exile in Japan for his participation in the "Second Revolution" against Yuan Shikai]

196
00:10:49,442 --> 00:10:51,000
[Zhang Tuzhao, styled Xing Yan, prominent social activist forced into exile in Japan for his participation in the "Second Revolution" against Yuan Shikai]
Yeah! That's right!

197
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,520
[Zhang Tuzhao, styled Xing Yan, prominent social activist forced into exile in Japan for his participation in the "Second Revolution" against Yuan Shikai]
Britain, Austria, Germany, Italy.

198
00:10:53,752 --> 00:10:55,440
Which country has not experienced this?

199
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,760
How many times has this happened?

200
00:10:57,038 --> 00:10:58,360
The sacrifices that have been made

201
00:10:58,443 --> 00:11:01,400
to achieve real social progress.

202
00:11:01,882 --> 00:11:03,200
Another thing I want to ask you is,

203
00:11:03,638 --> 00:11:05,000
what did you just say?

204
00:11:05,554 --> 00:11:09,040
Our country is not yet open-minded?

205
00:11:09,203 --> 00:11:11,040
That's demonstrably false!

206
00:11:11,704 --> 00:11:13,160
Since the Xinhai Revolution,

207
00:11:13,468 --> 00:11:14,960
the mindset of the entire population

208
00:11:15,154 --> 00:11:18,154
has changed dramatically.

209
00:11:18,546 --> 00:11:21,120
Judging from the unanimous rejection of Yuan at home and abroad,

210
00:11:21,330 --> 00:11:22,640
this is hard evidence.

211
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,960
The more the nation is at stake,

212
00:11:25,734 --> 00:11:28,000
the more the people should become aware of the situation.

213
00:11:28,184 --> 00:11:29,880
To revive the national spirit

214
00:11:30,266 --> 00:11:32,480
and if the idea of republicanism is to be put into practice

215
00:11:32,705 --> 00:11:33,560
for the people,

216
00:11:33,744 --> 00:11:36,600
it is necessary to overthrow the feudal ideology

217
00:11:36,974 --> 00:11:39,880
Zhang Fengzai, those who go against the tide of history

218
00:11:40,231 --> 00:11:42,720
will be drowned by the torrent of the times.

219
00:11:42,942 --> 00:11:44,280
For the love of our country,

220
00:11:44,719 --> 00:11:47,200
we want to save our country. Down with Yuan.

221
00:11:47,857 --> 00:11:50,000
For the sake of our Chinese nation,

222
00:11:50,455 --> 00:11:53,455
we must save our country. Down with Yuan!

223
00:11:53,821 --> 00:12:01,920
Save the country! Down with Yuan!

224
00:12:02,068 --> 00:12:02,880
Well said!

225
00:12:03,975 --> 00:12:04,720
Well said!

226
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:07,120
Professor Xing Yan.

227
00:12:08,785 --> 00:12:09,360
Hello students.

228
00:12:09,941 --> 00:12:10,920
The usual words:

229
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:13,800
well-reasoned, from the heart,

230
00:12:14,436 --> 00:12:16,760
passionate, engaging.

231
00:12:17,340 --> 00:12:17,960
Very good.

232
00:12:18,624 --> 00:12:21,040
Zhong Fu, what do you think?

233
00:12:21,415 --> 00:12:23,040
Zhong Fu? Chen Duxiu?

234
00:12:24,141 --> 00:12:25,200
It's Chen Duxiu!

235
00:12:25,468 --> 00:12:26,400
Chen Duxiu!

236
00:12:27,599 --> 00:12:28,720
Is it Chen Duxiu?

237
00:12:28,841 --> 00:12:30,200
Why does he look like that?

238
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,400
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhong Fu, revolutionary forced into exile in Japan for his participation in the "Second Revolution" against Yuan Shikai]

239
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,720
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhong Fu, revolutionary forced into exile in Japan for his participation in the "Second Revolution" against Yuan Shikai]
Could it be Chen Duxiu?

240
00:12:33,400 --> 00:12:34,200
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhong Fu, revolutionary forced into exile in Japan for his participation in the "Second Revolution" against Yuan Shikai]
It can't be.

241
00:12:35,794 --> 00:12:37,000
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhong Fu, revolutionary forced into exile in Japan for his participation in the "Second Revolution" against Yuan Shikai]
As you said,

242
00:12:37,496 --> 00:12:39,080
a very knowledgeable young man.

243
00:12:39,416 --> 00:12:40,120
Chen Duxiu.

244
00:12:41,158 --> 00:12:42,840
Why are you eating here?

245
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:43,920
I was just passing by

246
00:12:44,434 --> 00:12:45,600
seeing them bickering.

247
00:12:45,655 --> 00:12:46,520
No one was eating.

248
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:49,080
One should never waste food at any time.

249
00:12:49,376 --> 00:12:50,720
It's shameful to waste food

250
00:12:51,822 --> 00:12:54,120
What time is it? You're still eating here?

251
00:12:57,831 --> 00:12:59,040
Are you Chen Duxiu?

252
00:13:00,098 --> 00:13:01,600
I am, yes.

253
00:13:01,754 --> 00:13:02,320
He really is!

254
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,400
I am Chen Duxiu.

255
00:13:05,496 --> 00:13:06,320
He is! He's Chen Duxiu!

256
00:13:06,354 --> 00:13:07,480
Quiet, everyone!

257
00:13:08,734 --> 00:13:09,240
Quiet!

258
00:13:10,574 --> 00:13:11,920
Since Mr. Zhong Fu is here,

259
00:13:12,438 --> 00:13:13,400
we would like to ask you:

260
00:13:13,739 --> 00:13:16,280
what do you think should be done to save China?

261
00:13:16,954 --> 00:13:17,800
I think that

262
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,880
such a country is irredeemable.

263
00:13:19,916 --> 00:13:20,880
What did you say?

264
00:13:21,350 --> 00:13:23,400
Are you Chinese? How can you say that?

265
00:13:25,774 --> 00:13:27,960
Chen Duxiu, are you talking about people?

266
00:13:28,218 --> 00:13:29,600
Simply shameless!

267
00:13:30,621 --> 00:13:31,560
Shameless!

268
00:13:32,215 --> 00:13:32,840
What are you doing?

269
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,560
You've gone too far!

270
00:13:35,574 --> 00:13:37,800
Mr. Zhong Fu, what you just said,

271
00:13:38,159 --> 00:13:39,560
do you really believe that?

272
00:13:40,275 --> 00:13:41,320
Yes, of course.

273
00:13:41,596 --> 00:13:43,080
But yeah, I meant to say...

274
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,320
You see?!

275
00:13:44,838 --> 00:13:46,880
Students! You have seen it!

276
00:13:47,238 --> 00:13:49,080
This is what you call a revolutionary party!

277
00:13:49,709 --> 00:13:50,880
Behold, the great revolutionary!

278
00:13:51,235 --> 00:13:52,720
Do you know what he said?

279
00:13:53,118 --> 00:13:55,120
He said he was sorry for his country's subjugation.

280
00:13:55,212 --> 00:13:56,120
What else?

281
00:13:56,477 --> 00:13:59,360
What is the horror of being a slave to a fallen nation?

282
00:13:59,864 --> 00:14:02,864
A country of a brutalized people, where is the love for it?

283
00:14:04,220 --> 00:14:07,760
This is the real traitor, a hanjian!

284
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:09,120
Traitor! Hanjian!

285
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:10,440
Hanjian!

286
00:14:11,115 --> 00:14:12,440
Get out of the way!

287
00:14:12,823 --> 00:14:14,200
Don't do it!

288
00:14:15,324 --> 00:14:16,560
Let's have a good chat!

289
00:14:16,674 --> 00:14:17,440
Don't do it!

290
00:14:17,985 --> 00:14:19,160
Stop!

291
00:14:19,160 --> 00:14:20,880
Don't do it!

292
00:14:21,183 --> 00:14:21,720
Don't do it!

293
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:23,000
Mr Zhong Fu, go!

294
00:14:23,189 --> 00:14:24,600
Don't do it!

295
00:14:25,223 --> 00:14:27,400
Let's have a good chat! Don't do it!

296
00:14:27,944 --> 00:14:29,360
Come on, this way!

297
00:14:29,440 --> 00:14:31,400
Don't do it, people, don't do it!

298
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,280
Listen to me for a moment!

299
00:14:32,280 --> 00:14:33,240
Mr. Xing Yan has a message for everyone!

300
00:14:33,434 --> 00:14:34,720
Mr. Xing Yan has a message for everyone!

301
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:36,200
Come on, everyone, let me tell you something!

302
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,320
Come on, come on!

303
00:14:52,583 --> 00:14:53,120
Alright.

304
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,120
Alright, alright, no one is following.

305
00:14:55,876 --> 00:14:56,640
Take a break, take a break.

306
00:15:19,758 --> 00:15:21,120
Not like Chen Duxiu, right?

307
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:25,520
I just imagined

308
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:26,760
something a little different.

309
00:15:27,405 --> 00:15:29,120
So what do you imagine it should be like?

310
00:15:29,981 --> 00:15:30,800
Are you okay?

311
00:15:32,076 --> 00:15:34,560
I apologise for the situation.

312
00:15:34,981 --> 00:15:37,981
It's okay, I've seen a lot of these.

313
00:15:41,174 --> 00:15:41,702
Your article

314
00:15:41,702 --> 00:15:44,520
"Patriotism and Self-consciousness", I've read it.

315
00:15:45,162 --> 00:15:47,040
But there are many doubts and unanswered questions.

316
00:15:47,389 --> 00:15:49,120
I would like to ask you some, is that okay?

317
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,960
I know that you, Li Dazhao, are from Hebei.

318
00:15:52,345 --> 00:15:55,345
Yanzhao is a land of compassion and tragedy, I must confess.

319
00:15:55,755 --> 00:15:56,800
But now in China

320
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,640
there is a shortage of real men who believe in the truth.

321
00:15:59,160 --> 00:15:59,960
Ask.

322
00:16:00,159 --> 00:16:02,840
You said that patriotism should have a stand

323
00:16:02,899 --> 00:16:04,560
and not be willing to be Yuan Shikai's obedient people

324
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:06,400
in the name of patriotism.

325
00:16:07,054 --> 00:16:09,080
According to you,

326
00:16:09,345 --> 00:16:10,760
as long as Yuan Shikai is in power,

327
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:12,040
people should not be patriotic.

328
00:16:13,550 --> 00:16:16,160
You misunderstood the reasoning behind it.

329
00:16:16,455 --> 00:16:18,000
I meant to say,

330
00:16:18,309 --> 00:16:20,200
patriotism should have a position.

331
00:16:20,696 --> 00:16:23,240
You can't link patriotism with loyalty to Yuan Shikai.

332
00:16:23,335 --> 00:16:24,320
You can't confuse

333
00:16:24,433 --> 00:16:25,840
patriotism with loyalty to Yuan Shikai

334
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:28,640
to cover up Yuan Shikai's theft of the country.

335
00:16:28,995 --> 00:16:30,280
This is similar to what you just said,

336
00:16:30,505 --> 00:16:31,440
is it not?

337
00:16:31,893 --> 00:16:32,880
This Yuan Shikai

338
00:16:32,953 --> 00:16:35,720
claims that he represents the country.

339
00:16:36,098 --> 00:16:37,840
He is confusing the idea.

340
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:41,000
If patriotism has no position,

341
00:16:41,574 --> 00:16:43,240
then we simply have no reason

342
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,000
to defeat Yuan Shikai.

343
00:16:45,044 --> 00:16:46,480
I agree.

344
00:16:46,829 --> 00:16:48,480
I think the first priority today is

345
00:16:48,585 --> 00:16:51,160
to inspire the people to be truly patriotic.

346
00:16:51,869 --> 00:16:54,320
Right now China is being divided up by the Western powers.

347
00:16:54,502 --> 00:16:55,840
If we are not patriotic,

348
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:56,840
then the country will die.

349
00:16:57,915 --> 00:16:59,960
Shou Chang, I ask you:

350
00:17:00,229 --> 00:17:03,229
What did the Western powers rely on to carve up China?

351
00:17:03,453 --> 00:17:04,320
Gunboats.

352
00:17:04,398 --> 00:17:04,960
No.

353
00:17:05,305 --> 00:17:07,454
You are talking about the Opium War and the Sino-Japanese War.

354
00:17:07,823 --> 00:17:11,235
Now the powers are dividing China by borrowing money.

355
00:17:12,224 --> 00:17:13,170
The Chinese government

356
00:17:13,302 --> 00:17:16,550
borrows foreign debt from Western countries every year.

357
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,808
More than half of the treasury's revenue,

358
00:17:19,434 --> 00:17:21,087
in a country without productivity.

359
00:17:22,275 --> 00:17:25,510
The state can only be maintained

360
00:17:25,510 --> 00:17:27,390
by borrowing against the national tax railroad.

361
00:17:27,866 --> 00:17:29,782
What do you expect from a country like this?

362
00:17:30,064 --> 00:17:32,270
That's why we're going to overthrow Yuan,

363
00:17:32,592 --> 00:17:34,192
overthrow this corrupt government,

364
00:17:34,351 --> 00:17:35,544
and build a new nation.

365
00:17:35,703 --> 00:17:36,080
No!

366
00:17:38,144 --> 00:17:40,027
China can be saved by political revolution.

367
00:17:40,317 --> 00:17:41,920
China's problems are accumulating.

368
00:17:42,263 --> 00:17:44,469
Can we solve the problem by changing people and governments?

369
00:17:46,268 --> 00:17:47,509
So, according to you,

370
00:17:47,509 --> 00:17:49,262
China has no way out?

371
00:17:49,422 --> 00:17:52,184
Yes, but the way out is not the old way.

372
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:55,032
The way out is a new way.

373
00:17:55,917 --> 00:17:56,845
China will not die.

374
00:17:57,349 --> 00:17:57,950
What is the old way?

375
00:17:58,425 --> 00:17:59,383
The dynastic cycle:

376
00:17:59,753 --> 00:18:00,640
the overthrow of an old dynasty,

377
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:01,643
the establishment of a new dynasty.

378
00:18:01,782 --> 00:18:03,246
The cycle repeats itself. It's the old way.

379
00:18:03,390 --> 00:18:04,388
And what is the new way?

380
00:18:04,550 --> 00:18:05,193
Don't know.

381
00:18:11,716 --> 00:18:12,382
That's what I'm looking for.

382
00:18:13,729 --> 00:18:16,262
Shou Chang, I appreciate your knowledge and talent.

383
00:18:16,782 --> 00:18:18,317
Will you look for this new path with me?

384
00:18:19,263 --> 00:18:21,520
To find a way to save China

385
00:18:21,954 --> 00:18:24,062
is my life's work.

386
00:18:24,742 --> 00:18:25,719
I will.

387
00:18:26,757 --> 00:18:27,716
Good.

388
00:18:32,439 --> 00:18:33,474
Zhong Fu!

389
00:18:36,182 --> 00:18:37,915
You've both come here

390
00:18:38,063 --> 00:18:39,707
and made us look for you!

391
00:18:39,942 --> 00:18:41,746
Tickets... we have the tickets.

392
00:18:42,401 --> 00:18:43,889
Tomorrow we can go back home.

393
00:18:45,098 --> 00:18:47,631
Excellent. Finally we can go back.

394
00:18:47,949 --> 00:18:50,481
Zhong Fu, before I go back,

395
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:52,189
I finally got to see Shou Chang.

396
00:18:53,064 --> 00:18:54,913
It's not in vain that you have been charged

397
00:18:55,068 --> 00:18:56,626
with being a traitor to the country.

398
00:18:56,782 --> 00:18:58,187
Not in vain... not in vain...

399
00:18:59,461 --> 00:19:00,199
See me?

400
00:19:01,193 --> 00:19:01,902
Yeah.

401
00:19:02,469 --> 00:19:04,266
He's here to see you today.

402
00:19:05,048 --> 00:19:06,601
Ever since he was on the "Kaiyin",

403
00:19:06,601 --> 00:19:08,170
and read your article,

404
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:10,229
he's been wanting to see you.

405
00:19:10,504 --> 00:19:11,305
It was worth the trip.

406
00:19:11,571 --> 00:19:14,399
A great harvest, a great treasure.

407
00:19:16,194 --> 00:19:18,582
You... You are always bored in the room writing articles

408
00:19:18,713 --> 00:19:19,555
not letting us control

409
00:19:19,555 --> 00:19:20,425
nor letting us ask,

410
00:19:20,425 --> 00:19:22,186
making yourself like a beggar.

411
00:19:22,383 --> 00:19:23,039
I've got lice all over my body.

412
00:19:23,039 --> 00:19:23,978
[Yi Baisha, styled Yue Chuan, famous thinker forced into exile in Japan for participating in the "Second Revolution" against Yuan Shikai]
I've got lice all over my body.

